CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 8, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Pittsburghers Enjoy a Sporting Holiday Weekend - In The Well! - Leroy Stevens of the Kennard Swimming Pool team does a graceful back dive into the 'well' at the Highland Park swimming pool during a city-wide meet Labor Day.  The meet was sponsored by the Sun-Telegraph and the Bureau of Recreation.  Sepia swimmers represented Kennard, Centre Ave. YMCA and Clairton. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Leroy Stevens performing back dive at Highland Park swimming pool during swim meet
